{"body": "Just a :+1: from those of us out here in user land.  I ran into this issue 20 minutes ago and hacked up a quick monkey patch for my app running on 3.2.9.  I was going to try my hand at my first PR for Rails when I decided to check Edge and, lo and behold, there it was!\r\n\r\nI concur with @jeremy and @marcandre.  I actually had to go look at the source to discover that `to: 'self.class'` was a workaround for 3.2.9 (I had figured out that `class_eval` was probably being used, but still didn't know the shape of the code on the inside), and I think it's prettier to be able to use `to: :class`.  ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11844733", "created_at": "2013-01-03T14:14:51Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7613#issuecomment-11844733", "updated_at": "2013-01-03T14:14:51Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7613, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/tovodeverett", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/56f270b44be8b798730e44d080348035?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ffc75f145e028a71cff2f944ae1f263d9.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/received_events", "gravatar_id": "56f270b44be8b798730e44d080348035", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "tovodeverett", "type": "User", "id": 2568894, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tovodeverett/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f9c4bd3543c15100b501"